displayName: Block JavaScript or VBScript from launching downloaded executable content
description: When set to Yes, Defender will block Javascript or VBScript files that have been downloaded from the Internet from being executed. When set to Audit only, Windows events will be raised instead of blocking. Setting to Not Configured will return the setting to Windows default, which is off. This attack surface reduction (ASR) rule is controlled via the following GUID: D3E037E1-3EB8-44C8-A917-57927947596D
